library(magrittr)
library(MASS)
library(car)
library(alr3)
library(corrplot)
library(tidyverse)

Data

This data set comes from the UCI Machine Learning Repository and can be found here. According to the data abstract, this data set consists of posts published during the year of 2014 on the Facebook pages of a renowned cosmetics brand. The data set contains 500 rows and 19 variables about each post.

facebook <- read.csv(file = '../data/Facebook_metrics/dataset_Facebook.csv', sep = ';')
facebook <-
  facebook %>%
  na.omit()
facebook %>% 
  select(!type) %>%
  cor() %>%
  corrplot.mixed(order = "hclust", tl.col = "black")

stepAIC(lm(consumers ~ 
             category +
             total_page_likes +
             type +
             month_posted +
             hour_posted +
             weekday_posted +
             paid,
           data = facebook),
        trace = FALSE)$anova

model <- lm(consumers ~ 
     category +
     total_page_likes + 
     type +
     weekday_posted +
     paid,
   data = facebook)
par(mfrow = c(2,2))
plot(model)

facebook %>% 
  select(consumers,
         category,
         total_page_likes,
         weekday_posted,
         paid) %>%
  powerTransform(family = 'yjPower')
## Estimated transformation parameters 
##        consumers         category total_page_likes   weekday_posted 
##        0.1039487       -0.1907310        5.4815911        0.8330330 
##             paid 
##       -4.3314030
transformed_model <- lm(log(consumers) ~
                          category +
                          total_page_likes +
                          type +
                          weekday_posted +
                          paid,
                        data = facebook)
summary(transformed_model)
